Marketing & Media:
   U.S.'s Consumption
   Of Newsprint Climbed
   By 0.5% in November
The association said newsprint consumption by U.S. daily
newspapers fell 5.3% in November to 724,182 metric tons from
764,796 metric tons a year earlier. For the first 11 months,
newsprint consumption by U.S. daily newspapers fell 7.1% to
7,584,301 metric tons from 8,161,821 metric tons in the
year-earlier period.
   Newsprint inventories of newspapers in the association's
statistical sample averaged a 41-day supply in November
compared with a 38-day supply a year earlier.
   The association said Canadian newsprint mills operated at
81% of rated capacity in November and 86% for the 11 months,
while U.S. newsprint mills operated at 97.3% of rated
capacity in November and 95.4% for the 11 months.